abstract: >
Ecological Field Theory of Hybrid Cognitive Intelligence (EFT–HCI) presents a
formal mathematical framework for modeling interaction as a constrained
dynamical field. The theory describes structure at the level of
human–system interaction under conditions of constraint and coherence,
rather than attributing intelligence to any single system.

The framework develops a unified formalism spanning manifolds, tensor
fields, operator dynamics, and spectral structure, and characterizes
stability, attractors, phase transitions, and collapse within the
interactional field.

